Here may be a solution, @Karmylr feel free to try it.

Since some JS rules may not work properly on iOS, I found several iOS browser with the support of userscript, such as via, alook, and several applications which give userscript support for Safari.
I tried with via, and add a script as follows:

```
// ==UserScript==
// @name         NiVod without AD
// @namespace    https://viayoo.com/
// @version      0.1
// @description  Remove the video AD of nivod/mudvod, the code is extracted from AdGuard Chinese filter. More details please refer https://github.com/AdguardTeam/AdguardFilters/issues/146359
// @author       MoienBowen
// @run-at       document-start
// @match       https://m.nivod4.tv/*
// @grant         none
// ==/UserScript==

(function(){
	window.eval=new Proxy(eval,{apply:(a,b,c)=>{if(c[0]&&c[0].includes("commercial")&&c[0].startsWith("(")&&c[0].endsWith(")")){let a=c[0].slice(1).slice(0,-1),b=JSON.parse(a);b.entity?.commercial&&(b.entity.commercial=void 0),c[0]=`(${JSON.stringify(b)})`}return Reflect.apply(a,b,c)}})})();
```

Look forward to your feedback.
And thanks again @AdamWr for your rules.

